Date: Wed 10 Jul 2013
Source: WCSH 6 Portland [edited]
http://www.wcsh6.com/news/national/article/249187/44/Legionnaires-outbreak


Dozens of cases of Legionnaires' disease have been reported across the metro Detroit area [Michigan]. Investigations are being conducted to determine common sources of exposure.

Meanwhile, the Oakland County Health division is strongly advising that residents take all necessary steps to prevent the disease, which is a respiratory infection caused by bacteria called _Legionella_.

[Byline: Michele Mullen]

