[2]
Date: Sat 6 Jul 2013
Source: Detroit Free Press [edited]
http://www.freep.com/article/20130706/NEWS05/307060019/Legionnaires-disease


State health officials are investigating an uptick in cases of Legionnaires' disease in metro Detroit.

A total of 35 cases were reported in June [2013], said Angela Minicuci, public information officer for the Michigan Department of Community Health. They were in Wayne and Macomb counties and the city of Detroit. "Around this time of year, this is when we would see a typical seasonal increase," Minicuci said. "The numbers are just a little bit higher than what we're typically used to seeing in June."

Of the 15 cases of Legionnaires' disease reported so far this year [2013] in Wayne County outside of Detroit, 13 were in June, said Mary Mazur, spokeswoman for the Wayne County Department of Public Health. "The investigation is ongoing," she said. "As of this time, we have not found a common thread."

[Byline: Ann Zaniewski]

